define("STR_PRISMA_NOMBRE_INFORME_NARRATIVO_TXT", "Expert Narrative Report");
define("PRISMA_NARRATIVO_INTP1", "This report is based on responses from Mr / Ms. @usuario@ to a self-assessment questionnaire: the Prisma professional skills and personality questionnaire. The questionnaire invites the subject to describe their behaviour, preferences and attitudes regarding various aspects of their working lives. ");
define("PRISMA_NARRATIVO_INTP2", "The subject was asked to choose from groups of three statements of behaviour patterns in the work environment the statement that 1) best and 2) worst fits his/her attitudes or personality. Their responses were compared with those of a broad and analogous sample to obtain a profile of the perceived preferences of Mr / Ms. @usuario@ in respect of the different ways of behaving at work, grouped into four main areas: energy and motivation, emotional control and stress tolerance, relationships with people, thinking style and potential mental resources. ");
define("PRISMA_NARRATIVO_INTP3", "This report describes the personality profile of Mr / Ms. @usuario@ and should be treated as confidential. Considering the results of the questionnaire, it is important to note that this represents their vision of themselves and how he/she perceive his/her own behaviour, as opposed to the way another might describe his/her personality. The accuracy of this report depends on the frankness and sincerity with which they completed the questionnaire, together with his own self-knowledge. Therefore, the comments made in this report should be considered as something indicative, reliable, though not infallible. This 'self-report' can provide significant indicators as to the style of Mr / Mrs. @usuario@ at work, and is likely to allow us to predict to a great extent his/her behaviour in different situations. ");
define("PRISMA_NARRATIVO_INTP4", "Please note that the questionnaire describes the behaviour style that Mr / Ms. @usuario@ prefers: not their abilities. The questionnaire provides a comprehensive picture of his/her current style and, therefore, the report is necessarily general. The lifetime of the data contained in the report is considered to be between 18 and 24 months, depending on personal circumstances and the workplace. If significant changes have occurred in his/her life or if there is a significant change in the position, he/she should complete the questionnaire again. ");
define("PRISMA_NARRATIVO_INTP5", "If you have any concerns regarding the content of this report, approach someone who has been fully trained in the use of the Prism questionnaire.");
